Reasoning: The paper focuses on the digitization process of an early printed book using OCR and layout analysis, which falls under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The use of automated layout analysis also involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the human effort required for the digitization process, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL) in terms of text recognition.
